ZH: 不要骚扰我，我正在工作。
EN: Do not disturb me, I am working.

ZH: 他被对方不断骚扰，感到非常烦恼。
EN: He was constantly harassed by the other party, feeling very upset.

ZH: 她总是会遭到社交媒体上的骚扰。
EN: She always faces harassment on social media.

ZH: 学校已经制定了严格的规定，禁止任何形式的骚扰。
EN: The school has established strict regulations prohibiting any form of harassment.

ZH: 警方正在调查这起恶意骚扰事件。
EN: The police are investigating this case of malicious harassment.

ZH: 请你停止对他的骚扰。
EN: Please stop harassing him.

ZH: 每当他开车经过我家时，都会发出很大的噪音，骚扰了整个社区。
EN: Whenever he drives by my house, he makes a lot of noise, disturbing the whole community.

ZH: 她因被同事骚扰而感到不安。
EN: She felt uneasy because she was harassed by her colleagues.

ZH: 对方对她进行了性骚扰。
EN: The other party sexually harassed her.

ZH: 他恼羞成怒地对我进行了一番骚扰。
EN: He angrily harassed me.

ZH: 这样的行为已经构成骚扰。
EN: Such behavior constitutes harassment.

ZH: 我已经向警方报告了这起骚扰事件。
EN: I have reported this harassment incident to the police.

ZH: 他被对方频繁骚扰，最终选择了离职。
EN: He was harassed frequently by the other party and eventually chose to resign.

ZH: 这种形式的骚扰是不可容忍的。
EN: This form of harassment is intolerable.

ZH: 她的电话不断被骚扰，导致她很烦恼。
EN: Her phone is constantly being harassed, causing her a lot of distress.

ZH: 老板的言论引起了员工的骚扰。
EN: The boss's remarks caused harassment to the employees.

ZH: 骚扰行为已经严重侵犯了他的权益。
EN: The harassing behavior has seriously infringed on his rights.

ZH: 她选择保持沉默，不想再被骚扰。
EN: She chose to remain silent and did not want to be harassed again.

ZH: 我们要建立一个无骚扰的工作环境。
EN: We want to create a harassment-free work environment.

ZH: 不要因为过于热情而对对方进行骚扰。
EN: Do not harass the other party with excessive enthusiasm.
